## 13. SUMMARY OF ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS

| Pattern | Implementation | Evidence |
|---------|----------------|----------|
| **Clean Architecture** | ✅ Strict 4-layer (Domain/Use Case/Interface/Infrastructure) | Consistent across all modules |
| **DDD** | ✅ Domain models with invariants, aggregates, value objects | `ImportJob` with state transitions |
| **Ports & Adapters** | ✅ Input/Output ports as interfaces | `AnalyzeSecurityInputPort`, `LLMServicePort` |
| **CQRS** | ⚠️ Partial (separate read/write repos, no event sourcing) | Query vs command methods in repos |
| **Dependency Injection** | ✅ uber-go/dig with module-level providers | All modules have `di/provider.go` |
| **Repository Pattern** | ✅ Interfaces in domain, PostgreSQL implementations | Complete with DB model mapping |
| **Error Handling** | ✅ Sentinel errors + Coded errors with HTTP status | Domain errors + CodedError with codes |
| **Multi-Tenancy** | ✅ Context-based tenant isolation | `TenantDBManager.ForTenantOrDefault()` |
| **Idempotency** | ✅ Check-before-create pattern in use cases | `analyzeConversationInteractor.AnalyzeConversation()` |
| **API Documentation** | ✅ Technical design docs | `/docs/02-technical/03_clean_architecture_dto_mapping.md` |

---

This comprehensive architecture enables:
- **Testability** — All layers mockable via interfaces
- **Maintainability** — Clear separation of concerns
